{"parse":{"title":"Llibre del Repartiment (Majorca)","pageid":37942076,"revid":818626569,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the land distribution document for <a href=\"/wiki/Majorca\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Majorca\">Majorca</a>. For the land distribution document for Valencia, see <a href=\"/wiki/Llibre_del_Repartiment_(Valencia)\" title=\"Llibre del Repartiment (Valencia)\">Llibre del Repartiment (Valencia)</a>.</div>\n<p>The <b>Llibre del Repartiment</b> is a record book in which the king's scribes recorded the pledges of properties at the completion of a conquest. The document includes only properties that were ceded to the monarch after the <a href=\"/wiki/Conquest_of_Majorca\" title=\"Conquest of Majorca\">conquest of the island of Majorca</a> in 1229.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It meticulously recorded the houses or land donations made by <a href=\"/wiki/James_I_of_Aragon\" title=\"James I of Aragon\">James I</a> to the <a href=\"/wiki/Aragonese_people\" title=\"Aragonese people\">Aragonese</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Catalan_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Catalan people\">Catalan</a> nobles and ultimately to all who participated in the crusade for the conquest of <a href=\"/wiki/Majorca\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Majorca\">Majorca</a>. Of course, the properties had been expropriated from the Muslims who had previously inhabited the island of Majorca.\n</p><p>This book is kept in the \"l'Arxiu del Regne de Mallorca\" in the city of <a href=\"/wiki/Palma,_Majorca\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Palma, Majorca\">Palma</a>, but actually consists of two volumes: one bilingual in <a href=\"/wiki/Latin_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Latin language\">Latin</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Arabic_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arabic language\">Arabic</a>, and another in <a href=\"/wiki/Catalan_language\" title=\"Catalan language\">Catalan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The groups that had greater involvement in the company were Barcelona and Marseille, the first with a total of 877 horses and the second with 636, followed by the <a href=\"/wiki/Knights_Templar\" title=\"Knights Templar\">Knights Templar</a> which had 525.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Llibre_del_Repartiment_(Majorca)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Llibre_del_Repartiment_(Valencia)\" title=\"Llibre del Repartiment (Valencia)\">Llibre del Repartiment (Valencia)</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Llibre_del_Repartiment_(Majorca)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Guillem Rosell\u00f3 Bordoy (2003). \"El Recuerdo de la Angig\u00fcedad Cl\u00e1sica en el Pepartiment de Mallorca\". Mayurqa. pp.&#160;225\u2013234.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=El+Recuerdo+de+la+Angig%C3%BCedad+Cl%C3%A1sica+en+el+Pepartiment+de+Mallorca&amp;rft.pages=225-234&amp;rft.pub=Mayurqa&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.au=Guillem+Rosell%C3%B3+Bordoy&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALlibre+del+Repartiment+%28Majorca%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> <span style=\"display:none;font-size:100%\" class=\"error citation-comment\">Missing or empty <code style=\"color:inherit; border:inherit; padding:inherit;\">&#124;url=</code> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#cite_web_url\" title=\"Help:CS1 errors\">help</a>)</span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">CCRTV. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110205022519/http://www.tv3.cat/historiesdecatalunya/documents/doc107074102.htm\">\"Llibre del repartiment (thirteenth century)\"</a> (in Catalan). Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tv3.cat/historiesdecatalunya/documents/doc107074102.htm\">the original</a> on 5 February 2011<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 October</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Llibre+del+repartiment+%28thirteenth+century%29&amp;rft.au=CCRTV&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tv3.cat%2Fhistoriesdecatalunya%2Fdocuments%2Fdoc107074102.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALlibre+del+Repartiment+%28Majorca%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Guillem Rosell\u00f3 Bordoy. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dialnet.unirioja.es/servlet/fichero_articulo?codigo=2245420...0\">\"Mallorca 1232: Colectivos urbanos, \u00f3rdenes mili